  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Local Cooperation Fund (LCF) in Mexico</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Tanesque / Basic training in marginalized communities . The project focuses on finding new tools on bilingual and intercultural training in rural and marginalized communities in four states (Puebla, Chipas, Oaxaca, Distrito Federal) of Mexico. Within the project 16 young indigenous people are trained to work with the school children. Later on, and based on a diagnosis of the learning processes of a pilote group of children, learning material appropriate for bilingual learning and for those with learning difficulties is produced in the languages of N&#xC3;&#xA1;huatl, Tseltal and Spanish. The project will last for three years.</narrative>
  </description>
